.TH sysopctl 1 "July 2024" "v0.1.0" "System Operations"
.SH NAME
sysopctl \- A command-line tool for system operations
.SH SYNOPSIS
sysopctl [option] [arguments]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This command is used for managing system services, processes, and health.
.SH OPTIONS
--help                 Show help message
--version              Show command version
service list           List running services
system load            Show system load averages
service start <name>   Start a service
service stop <name>    Stop a service
disk usage             Show disk usage
process monitor        Monitor system processes
logs analyze           Analyze system logs
backup <path>          Backup system files
.SH EXAMPLES
sysopctl service list
sysopctl system load
sysopctl service start apache2
